Data Preprocessiong¶

In [ ]:
# Combined the datasets together
dfs = [vix, consumer_sentiment, baa, delinquency_rate, home_price_index, inflation, 
       interest_rate, mbs, junkbonds, mortgage_rate, nasdaq, house_loan, sp500, unemployment]
for df in dfs:
    df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date']) # convert data to datetime.
combined_data = dfs[0]
for df in dfs[1:]:
    combined_data = combined_data.merge(df, on="Date", how="outer")

# Clean the combined dataset
combined_data.replace(".", pd.NA, inplace=True)
banklist.columns = banklist.columns.str.strip() 
combined_data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(combined_data['Date'])

# The columns with filled out data only have weekly, monthly, and quarterly values. 
# To add daily data, the daily values is populated with the corresponding monthly or weekly value for that period
# Fill monthly data
combined_data.set_index('Date', inplace=True)
monthly_columns = ['sentiment_index', 'inflation_rate', 'home_price_index', 'house_loan_rate', 'unemp_rate']
for col in monthly_columns:
    combined_data[col] = combined_data[col].resample('MS').ffill()
combined_data[monthly_columns] = combined_data[monthly_columns].ffill()

# Fill weekly data
combined_data['mbs_million'] = combined_data['mbs_million'].ffill(limit=4)
combined_data['mortgage_rate'] = combined_data['mortgage_rate'].ffill(limit=4)

# Fill quarterly data
combined_data['delinquency_rate'] = combined_data['delinquency_rate'].resample('QS').ffill().resample('MS').ffill(limit=2)
combined_data['delinquency_rate'] = combined_data['delinquency_rate'].ffill()

combined_data = combined_data.reset_index()
In [ ]:
# Filter the combined data to specific time range and main predictor
filtered_data = combined_data[(combined_data['Date'] >= '2000-01-01') & (combined_data['Date'] <= '2022-12-31')]
filtered_data = filtered_data.drop(['High', "Low", "Close"], axis=1)

# merge with the target dataset
banklist['FAILDATE'] = pd.to_datetime(banklist['FAILDATE'])
merged_df = pd.merge(filtered_data, banklist, how="left", left_on="Date", right_on="FAILDATE")
merged_df["Bank Failure"] = merged_df["FAILDATE"].notna().astype(int)

# Fill missing values in the Nasdaq index and closing price with the prior day's price due to the stock market being closed on weekends
merged_df['NASDAQ_index'] = merged_df['NASDAQ_index'].fillna(method='ffill')
merged_df['Adj_Close'] = merged_df['Adj_Close'].fillna(method='ffill')
merged_df = merged_df.drop(['NAME', 'FAILDATE', 'CERT', 'CITYST', 'CHCLASS1', 'RESTYPE','FIN','ID','RESTYPE1','SAVR'], axis=1)
merged_df[['QBFASSET','COST','QBFDEP']] = merged_df[['QBFASSET','COST','QBFDEP']].fillna(0)

# Convert data types
cols_to_convert = merged_df.columns.difference(['Bank Failure', 'Date'])
merged_df[cols_to_convert] = merged_df[cols_to_convert].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')

# Calculate the proportion of outliers
nd = df.select_dtypes(include=['float64', 'int64'])

def count_outliers(series):
    Q1 = series.quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = series.quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    outliers = ((series < (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) | (series > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR)))
    return np.sum(outliers)


total_outliers = nd.apply(count_outliers).sum()


proportion_of_outliers = total_outliers / (nd.shape[0] * nd.shape[1])
proportion_of_outliers

    ax1 = axes[i]
    ax1.plot(yearly_data.index, yearly_data[var], linewidth=1.5, label=var)
    ax1.set_ylabel('Rate (%)', fontsize=14)
    ax1.tick_params('y')
    ax1.legend(loc='upper left')

    ax2 = ax1.twinx()

    ax2.set_ylabel('Bank Failures', color='red', fontsize=14)
    ax2.tick_params('y', colors='red')
    ax2.legend(loc='upper right')

 
    if var == 'votality_rate':
        ax1.set_title('Chart 2: Annual Trend of Market Volatility and Bank Failures', fontsize=16)
    elif var == 'house_loan_rate':
        ax1.set_title('Chart 3: Yearly Comparison of Housing Loan Rates and Bank Failures', fontsize=16)
    elif var == 'delinquency_rate':
        ax1.set_title('Chart 4: Annual Trend of Delinquency Rates and Bank Failures', fontsize=16)

    ax1.set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=14)
  


plt.tight_layout()

from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

close_df = df[df['Type'] == 'Close']
merged_clean = close_df.drop(['Type', 'QBFASSET','COST','QBFDEP'], axis=1)

X = merged_clean.drop(['Date', 'Bank Failure'], axis=1)
y = merged_clean['Bank Failure']


scaler = StandardScaler()
X_standardized = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Check the first few rows of the standardized data
#pd.DataFrame(X_standardized, columns=X.columns).head()

# Apply PCA
pca = PCA()
principal_components = pca.fit_transform(X_standardized)
loadings = pd.DataFrame(pca.components_.T, columns=[f'PC{i+1}' for i in range(len(X.columns))], index=X.columns)

cumulative_explained_variance = np.cumsum(pca.explained_variance_ratio_)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

plt.grid(True)

from sklearn.utils import resample

data_pca = pd.concat([pd.DataFrame(X_pca), y.reset_index(drop=True)], axis=1)

pos_class = data_pca[data_pca['Bank Failure'] == 0].copy()
neg_class = data_pca[data_pca['Bank Failure'] == 1].copy()

neg_sample = resample(neg_class, replace=True, n_samples=len(pos_class), random_state=42)

data_balanced = pd.concat([pos_class, neg_sample])

data_balanced = data_balanced.sample(frac=1, random_state=42).reset_index(drop=True)


X_sampled = data_balanced.drop('Bank Failure', axis=1)
y_sampled = data_balanced['Bank Failure']

class ModelEvaluator:

  def __init__(self, X, y):
    self.X = X
    self.y = y

  def fit_and_evaluate(self, models):
    
    results = {}
    for name, model in models.items():
    
      
      scores = cross_val_score(model, X_pca, y, cv=5)
      results[name] = scores.mean()
      
      
      model.fit(self.X, self.y)
      
      
      y_pred = model.predict(X_tests)
      report = classification_report(y_tests, y_pred)
      results[name+'_report'] = report


    return results

  'DT': tree,
  'NB': nb_classifier,
  'KNN': knn_model,
  'LR': logreg_model
}

eval = ModelEvaluator(X_trains, y_trains)
results = eval.fit_and_evaluate(models)

def format_results(results):

  print("Cross validation mean:")
  for name, score in results.items():
    if 'report' not in name:
      print(f"{name}: {score:.3f}")

  print("\nClassification Reports:")
  for name, report in results.items():
    if 'report' in name:
      print(name)
      print(report)
      print()

format_results(results)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve, auc, roc_auc_score

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

for i, model in enumerate(models):
    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_tests)[:, 1]
    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_tests, y_prob)
    pr_auc = auc(recall, precision)
    model_name = models[i]
    plt.plot(recall, precision, label=f"{model_name} (AP = {pr_auc:0.2f})")
